TriggerLogic.Description: The barbarians respect only strength. Crush their leaders and demonstrate our power to bring the tribes under our control.
TriggerLogic.Title: Defeat Barbarians (0/5)

TriggerLogic.Message: Alright, it's time to make some heads roll. Remember, we only need to kill each of our foes' commanders to subdue them. Strike swiftly and decisively; it would be inadvisible to get tangled down in a protracted fight. And remember, defeating the barbarians lets us "borrow" some of their technology.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Dominatrix. No better way to destroy an enemy than make him your loyal servant.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
The Dominatrix hacks into enemy control systems and takes over an enemy unit, which can then be used like your own unit. More expensive units take longer to capture, while badly damaged units take less time. Multiple Dominatrices can capture a single unit more quickly.
After capturing a unit, a Dominatrix cannot fire again for 12 seconds. If a controlling Dominatrix is destroyed, any captured units attached to it are freed.
Unwanted units can be self-destructed (default hotkey: Ctrl+D).
We could use some mobile defense against enemy air attacks. Try building some Crashers from your factory.
The fast-moving Crasher fires a single short-range surface-to-air missile. Its armor and DPS are so-so.
Some more anti-air firepower seems warranted. I've uploaded the Chainsaw blueprints to your systems, Ada.

The Chainsaw provides a strong deterrant to air incursions with its long-range, highly lethal volleys of missiles. Be forewarned: it has low health for its cost and cannot defend itself from ground threats.
The enemy has some heavy defences. You could simply brute-force the, but that would be so... crude.
What do you propose?
Try an Impaler. Trouble-free neutralization of enemy structures from long range.

The Impaler launches a kinetic penetrator missile at long range, highly effective against static targets. The missile has essentially no AoE and cannot track its targets, so it relies on the target's position being known and unchanging.
You can self-destruct your own units (or captured enemy ones). The default hotkey is Ctrl+D.
Faithless heathen! I shall send you to the depths of the inferno myself!
The only person going to hell today is you, you self-righteous monomaniacal zealot!

Spring.KillTeam(1)

TriggerLogic.Message: Enough! When we next meet, you shall feel His fury, demon-spawn!
